      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KING ZEAL (1) promising type yet to be beaten in two tries. Jumped from the rails draw last time scoring by 1.3 lengths at Bulli (19.44). Has already won at this course. Rates to win again. FRENCH REVOLVER (2) has been mixing form lately, hitting the frame two back before finishing fifth (20.95) at this track in a Grade 5. Good beginner and aided by a handy draw. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. BLACK BEAR (4) comes off an average performance last start when fifth at this track over 365m behind Where's Ivy (21.01) in a Grade 4/5. Speedy beginner who can find the front with a clean break from the middle of the draw. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. ANGRY GOLIATH (7) form at this course and distance reads well.",
